Please understand I do not want to see innocent people die. What I want is for all possible evidence to be presented, evaluated, and a decision made. If that decision is guilty I do not see why I should support a convicted criminal to live the remander of his life in prison when the money could be better spent on education and programs to support America's youth to help prevent them from ending up on death row.<br>
<br>
I am just currious those that are participating in this debate, has anyone in your family or one of your close friends ever been the victim of a violent crime?<br>
<br>
My grandmother, (Mom's mother) was murdered when my mother was 4 months old.<br>
<br>
My cousin was shot at point blank range in the head by a woman with whom he had broken up with.<br>
<br>
Other violent crimes against my friends and family of a personal nature I will leave out for what should be obvious reasons.<br>
<br>
We can debate back and forth siting cases of injustice, but what it boils down to is this is all we have. Until a better system is found then what measures we can take to protect society should be taken. Prove yourself a menace to society then expect society to defend itself.<br>
<br>
I have reasons for believing the way I do. Am I bitter, no. Do I want to see justice served? Hell yes!<br>
<br>
